NAME
    gcloud beta service-directory locations describe - describe a location

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud beta service-directory locations describe LOCATION
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (BETA) Describe a location.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     Location resource - The Service Directory location to describe. This
     represents a Cloud resource. (NOTE) Some attributes are not given
     arguments in this group but can be set in other ways. To set the [project]
     attribute: provide the argument [location] on the command line with a
     fully specified name; set the property [core/project]. This must be
     specified.

       LOCATION
          ID of the location or fully qualified identifier for the location.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

EXAMPLES
    To describe a Service Directory location, run:

        $ gcloud beta service-directory locations describe location us-east1

NOTES
    This command is currently in BETA and may change without notice. This
    variant is also available:

        $ gcloud alpha service-directory locations describe

